== Description ==

The [[Image:Assembly_ConstraintPointsProjectDistance.svg|16px]] [[Assembly3_ConstraintPointsProjectDistance|Points project distance]] command constrains the distance of two 2D points in relation to a Straight line.

Based on the line's direction (the z axis of its implicit coordinate system (ICS)) setting the distance of two points along the line means to add the distance value to the first point's z value to receive the second point's z value (and ignoring the x and y values).

== Usage == 

# Select two points (2D or 3D).
# Select a straight line (2D or 3D).
# Activate the [[Image:Assembly_ConstraintPointsProjectDistance.svg|16px]] [[Assembly3_ConstraintPointsProjectDistance|Points project distance]] command using the:
#* {{Button|[[Image:Assembly_ConstraintPointsProjectDistance.svg|16px]] [[Assembly3_ConstraintPointsProjectDistance|Points project distance]]}} button.
# Press the {{Button|[[Image:Assembly3_workbench_icon.svg|16px]] [[Assembly3_ResolveConstraints|Solve constraints]]}} or the {{Button|[[Image:Assembly_QuickSolve.svg|16px]] [[Assembly3_QuickSolve|Quick solve]]}} button to recompute 
:: (if {{Button|[[Image:Assembly_AutoRecompute.svg|16px]] [[Assembly3_AutoRecompute|Auto recompute]]}} and {{Button|[[Image:Assembly_SmartRecompute.svg|16px]] [[Assembly3_SmartRecompute|Smart recompute]]}} are disabled).


